<span id="v.v.v-p1"></span><span class="c7"><span
id="v.v.v-p1.1"></span>Book III.</span>

<span id="v.v.v-p2"></span>*In this book Augustin refutes the second
letter* <span id="fr_2318"></span>[2319](#fn_2318.md) *which Petilianus
wrote to him after having seen the first of Augustin’s earlier books. 
This letter had been full of violent language; and Augustin rather shows
that the arguments of Petilianus had been deficient and irrelevant, than
brings forward arguments in support of his own statements.*

